MEASUREMENTS (
MM
). N = two males or eight females, mean (range). Length of body: male 20.03 (19.65–20.4), female 18.56 (15.6–20.6); length of fore wing: male 23.80 (23.5–24.1), female 24.23 (21.9–26.05); width of fore wing: male 8.55 (8.4–8.7), female 8.08 (7.0–9.05); length of head: male 3.40 (3.2–3.6), female 3.44 (3.05–3.8); width of head including eyes: male 7.63 (7.4–7.85), female 7.43 (6.6–7.95); width of pronotum including suprahumeral plates: male 7.03 (6.95–7.1), female 6.88 (5.85–7.65); width of mesonotum: male 6.18 (6.05–6.3), female 6.00 (5.1–6.7).
